usands of plastic spoons.<br /><br />Readers need not have seen <i>The Room</i> to appreciate its costar Greg Sestero’s account of how Tommy Wiseau defied every law of artistry, business, and interpersonal relationships to achieve the dream only he could love. While it does unravel mysteries for fans, <i>The Disaster Artist</i> is more than just an hilarious story about cinematic hubris: It is ultimately a surprisingly inspiring tour de force that reads like a page-turning novel, an open-hearted portrait of a supremely enigmatic man who will capture your heart.</span></div></div></div></div><div data-testid="genresList" class="BookPageMetadataSection__genres"><ul class="CollapsableList" aria-label="Top genres for this book"><span class="BookPageMetadataSection__genre"><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/genres/non-fiction" class="Button Button--tag-inline Button--medium"><span class="Button__labelItem">Nonfiction</span></a></span> <span class="BookPageMetadataSection__genre"><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/genres/memoir" class="Button Button--tag-inline Button--medium"><span class="Button__labelItem">Memoir</span></a></span> <span class="BookPageMetadataSection__genre"><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/genres/biography" class="Button Button--tag-inline Button--medium"><span class="Button__labelItem">Biography</span></a></span> <span class="BookPageMetadataSection__genre"><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/genres/film" class="Button Button--tag-inline Button--medium"><span class="Button__labelItem">Film</span></a></span> <div class="Button__container"><button type="button" class="Button Button--tag-inline Button--medium" aria-label="Show all items in the list"><span class="Button__labelItem">...more</span></button></div></ul></div><div class="BookDetails"><div class="CollapsableList"><span class="Text Text__body3"><div class="FeaturedDetails"><p data-testid="pagesFormat">270 pages, Hardcover</p><p data-testid="publicationInfo">First published October 1, 2013</p><p